  <h1 class="mb-4 text-danger">🛡️ Cybersecurity Trends in 2025</h1>
  <p class="lead">Cybersecurity in 2025 is not just about defense—it's about resilience, adaptability, and staying ahead of ever-evolving threats.</p>

  <h3 class="mt-5 text-warning">🔐 Rise of Zero Trust Architecture</h3>
  <p>Organizations are moving toward Zero Trust models, where no user or device is trusted by default. This shift ensures tighter access control and verification at every level.</p>

  <h3 class="mt-4 text-info">🤖 AI-Driven Threat Detection</h3>
  <p>Artificial Intelligence plays a major role in detecting and responding to cyber threats in real time. AI systems analyze behavior, flag anomalies, and help prevent breaches before they happen.</p>

  <h3 class="mt-4 text-success">🌐 Cloud Security Evolution</h3>
  <p>With the widespread adoption of cloud services, cloud-native security solutions are evolving. Encryption, access control, and continuous monitoring are essential for securing cloud infrastructure.</p>

  <h3 class="mt-4 text-primary">🧑‍💻 Human-Centric Security</h3>
  <p>Cybersecurity awareness training is more important than ever. Companies are investing in educating employees to recognize phishing attempts and social engineering tactics.</p>

  <h3 class="mt-4 text-secondary">📜 Global Cyber Laws and Compliance</h3>
  <p>Governments and organizations are establishing stronger cyber laws and compliance frameworks, making data protection a global priority in 2025.</p>
